
1. The official language is French. This is inherited from the colonial period and serves as an 
administrative language.The country has eight languages that are also classified as national 
languages.
2. Niger is on the border between Sahara and Sub-Sahara region.
3. Niger is considered one of the hottest nations. It is known as the “Frying Pan of the World.”
4. Niger borders seven countries.
5. Niger is home to the largest protected area in Africa. It covers  around 7.7 million hectares.
